TES4.SNAM:
Allows any number of mods to be configured from a single menu. Select "Mod Configuration" in the Start/Pause Menu.
Version 1.5

MESG.DESC:
Navigate the list on the left with &sXBDPadUp; and &sXBDPadDown;. Select a mod to configure with &sXBABtn;.
Press &sXBDPadRight; to move to the options for the selected mod. Press &sXBDPadLeft; to return to the mod list.

The Mod Configuration Menu has detected multiple menu entries for MCM. The mod will still function properly, but the pause menu loading time will be increased.
See the FAQ section of the readme for the solution.
DarNified UI has been detected in the HUD but not in the Start Menu. You will need to repair DarNified UI or remove it completely for The Mod Configuration Menu to appear correctly.
Navigate the list with &sXBDPadUp; and &sXBDPadDown;. Make your selection with &sXBABtn;.

Move the indicator with &sXBDPadLeft; or &sXBDPadRight; to decrease/increase the value.
Pressing &sXBLBumper; will move the indicator to the nearest mark on the left, while &sXBRBumper; will move it to the nearest mark on the right.

Select a meter to alter with &sXBDPadUp; or &sXBDPadDown;. The selected meter's indicator will be highlighted.
Move the indicator for the selected meter with &sXBDPadLeft; or &sXBDPadRight; to decrease/increase the value.
Pressing &sXBLBumper; will move the indicator to the nearest mark on the left, while &sXBRBumper; will move it to the nearest mark on the right.

NVSE cannot detect controller button presses at this time. You will need to use a program (e.g. XPadder) to simulate keyboard/mouse buttons with your controller for new hotkeys to work.
Press &sXBBBtn; to cancel.
The Mod Configuration Menu (MCM) has been installed.

The Mod Configuration Menu cannot access its menu files. Either the files are missing, an error has occurred with the NVSE plugin, or a firewall/UAC is preventing access.
You may need to reinstall the mod, update your 32-bit Visual C++ 2010 Redistributable Package, or change your firewall/UAC settings.
The Mod Configuration Menu has detected an unexpected version of menu files. You will need to reinstall MCM, overwriting any existing files.
The Mod Configuration Menu plugin has been renamed. This mod and those using it cannot function properly.
The Mod Configuration Menu has detected an older version of NVSE. NVSE Version 2.0 beta 12 or higher is required.
